34:16.679 --> 34:20.724
She had insurance for that.
Attention, morons.

34:20.809 --> 34:21.891
You went last year.

34:21.976 --> 34:24.770
You guys want Yankee tickets?
You wanna talk Yankee tickets?

34:24.855 --> 34:26.188
Yes.
Really.

34:26.273 --> 34:29.108
Okay, well, I wanna
see you dance for me.

34:29.192 --> 34:31.652
[Overlapping Chatter]

34:31.735 --> 34:33.654
You don't wanna dance?
I don't wanna embarrass you.

34:33.737 --> 34:36.322
I don't wanna embarrass you.
I'll just take this.
Everyone just go.

34:36.408 --> 34:39.869
I'll go talk to some kids
in the street. I see a little
bit there. That's pretty nice.

34:40.620 --> 34:42.580
That's it. The doctor
is giving me something.

34:42.664 --> 34:45.541
The doctor is giving me
some magic tapping there.

34:45.625 --> 34:48.293
Oh, I like that a lot.
Yeah, that's... Oh!

34:48.378 --> 34:51.797
All right, Little League,
you wanna go?
You want some of this?

34:51.882 --> 34:54.132
How's this, Ben?
This is dancing for tickets.
I'm dancing, Ben.

34:54.217 --> 34:56.135
Troy, sit on
the beanbag, please.
Hey, I started, Ben.

34:56.219 --> 34:58.387
Dance, dance, dance, dance

34:58.472 --> 35:00.014
Gerard, I guess
you don't want them, huh?

35:00.056 --> 35:02.641
This is worth tickets.
I'm not dancing.
This is totally stupid, man.

35:02.726 --> 35:05.519
Fine. Hey, hold out
for the Royals, huh?

35:09.232 --> 35:11.817
You are on
a total power trip,
you know that, man?

35:12.194 --> 35:13.611
This is totally
ridiculous, man.

35:13.695 --> 35:15.279
I was dancing first,
remember?

35:15.363 --> 35:17.948
You said dance,
I started dancing.

35:18.033 --> 35:21.452
You call that Yankee dancing?
No, no, that's like
Devil Ray dancing, okay?

35:21.536 --> 35:23.996
That's Devil Ray.
I'm talking about
Yankee dancing.

35:24.080 --> 35:28.000
That's what I'm talking about.
Yeah, get into it. Yeah!
How bad do you want it?

35:28.126 --> 35:30.753
Yeah, that's nice.
I love it. Come on in.
[Knocking]

35:30.837 --> 35:34.048
That's it!
Come on! Whoo!

35:34.132 --> 35:37.384
Latin hustle to

35:37.636 --> 35:39.345
Yowsah, yowsah, yowsah

35:39.429 --> 35:40.638
That's right. I'm...

35:40.722 --> 35:42.681
[Stops]

35:43.183 --> 35:45.518
Hey, what are you
doing here?

35:45.602 --> 35:47.436
I thought you weren't
coming in until tomorrow.
You look fantastic.

35:47.562 --> 35:50.189
I got in last night.
You know Troy,
Kevin and Gerard.

35:50.273 --> 35:53.025
Everyone else,
this is Lindsey.
Hi.

35:53.109 --> 35:54.109
Hi, Linds.

35:56.071 --> 35:57.988
Party?
No, it's draft day.

35:58.073 --> 36:01.534
This is the day we organize
the whole season, who gets
to go to what game with me.

36:01.618 --> 36:03.786
But don't worry.
You're still going
to opening day.

36:04.204 --> 36:07.957
Yeah, thank you.
Can I talk to you about
something really quickly?

36:08.041 --> 36:10.334
Sure, yeah, no problem.
Quick break, everybody.

36:10.418 --> 36:12.962
There's some nice
Pakistani cold cuts there,
courtesy of Mrs. Segal.

36:13.463 --> 36:16.006
I still don't think
they're worth
two Sunday tickets.

36:16.091 --> 36:17.925
Whoo-hoo!
Hey! Hey!

36:19.928 --> 36:21.762
Come here.

36:22.013 --> 36:23.764
Wait, I got you something.

36:23.848 --> 36:27.101
I set aside
some great games
for you too.

36:27.185 --> 36:30.646
Hmm? For when we go
to the games together.

36:31.106 --> 36:32.273
Thanks.

36:32.482 --> 36:34.608
It's what
the players wear.

36:35.527 --> 36:37.236
It's authentic.

36:40.323 --> 36:43.200
I gotta be honest.
This is getting me hot.

36:43.285 --> 36:48.539
Listen. Um, you know,
I saw you on ESPN.

36:48.623 --> 36:50.666
Oh. We looked like
morons, didn't we?

36:50.750 --> 36:54.920
Uh, yeah, yeah, total.
Not you so much, but...

36:55.005 --> 36:57.715
Well, it's very hot,
you know. It's Florida.

36:57.799 --> 36:59.800
[Chuckles]
You start seeing things.

37:00.218 --> 37:03.679
Um, you know, Ben,

37:03.763 --> 37:09.310
I didn't realize how big
this Red Sox thing is
with you.

37:09.769 --> 37:12.062
What?
Hey, I told you.

37:12.147 --> 37:14.648
See, this is...
This always happens.
Every time I...

37:14.733 --> 37:18.652
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
don't jump off a building.
We're just talking.

37:21.197 --> 37:24.408
Sorry. Knee jerk.
[Troy] Ben, come on, man.
The cold cuts are gone.

37:24.492 --> 37:27.244
Let's go in there.
Two minutes!

37:28.705 --> 37:30.873
Wow. I really hit
a nerve there, didn't I?

37:31.333 --> 37:33.500
Uh...
[Clears Throat]
Yeah.

37:33.835 --> 37:35.169
Come here.

37:36.338 --> 37:38.213
Thank you.

37:38.298 --> 37:42.301
I think there's
a better approach
to this whole Red Sox thing.

37:42.427 --> 37:45.137
Really?
Yeah. After all,
if I want this promotion,

37:45.221 --> 37:48.474
I am going to
have to push myself
really hard this summer.

37:48.558 --> 37:54.188
And I've never really been
very good at servicing myself,
my job and a relationship.

37:54.272 --> 37:56.940
Wait, wait.
We're not breaking up,
are we?

37:57.025 --> 37:59.818
No, no,
this is a good thing.
Okay.

37:59.903 --> 38:01.945
You're gonna be
so consumed with all of this

38:02.030 --> 38:04.073
that you won't
feel neglected all summer.

38:04.157 --> 38:06.158
No, no, yeah,
I'm not gonna
feel neglected.

38:06.242 --> 38:08.744
And I won't feel guilty
for having to do my job.

38:08.828 --> 38:10.496
Yeah, you shouldn't.

38:10.580 --> 38:13.916
So, what I'm saying is,
I think this is perfect.

38:14.000 --> 38:17.378
[Chuckles]
All right. Go, Sox!

38:17.962 --> 38:20.422
Two, three, four
Tessie

38:20.507 --> 38:22.466
Nuff Ced McGreevy shouted

38:22.550 --> 38:24.885
We're not here
to mess around

38:24.969 --> 38:28.347
We got 'em right here, folks.
Come on down. Cut your deficit
and balance your budget.

38:28.431 --> 38:31.141
Hear the crowd roar
to your sound

38:31.226 --> 38:33.143
Programs here!
Get your programs here!

38:33.228 --> 38:35.729
Don't blame us
if we ever doubt you

38:35.814 --> 38:38.565
You know we couldn't live
without you

38:39.234 --> 38:46.365
Tessie, you are
the only, only, only

38:48.952 --> 38:51.495
Hi. Hi.
Hey.

38:53.248 --> 38:55.791
[Man]
Peanuts! Cracker Jacks!

38:55.875 --> 38:59.044
Who wants peanuts?
Who wants Cracker Jacks?

38:59.129 --> 39:02.297
Peanuts! Cracker Jacks!
Who wants...

39:02.382 --> 39:04.550
It's unbelievable, right?
You can't even believe how...

39:04.634 --> 39:07.553
Look, right here, go.
This is it.
Thank you.

39:07.637 --> 39:11.348
Is this amazing?
Is this crazy? Would you
look at these seats?

39:11.433 --> 39:13.183
They're...
They're very red.

39:13.268 --> 39:15.686
No, I mean, their proximity
to the field.
This is Fenway Park.

39:15.770 --> 39:16.812
Oh.

39:16.896 --> 39:18.689
You can't buy these seats.
You have to,
like, inherit them.

39:18.773 --> 39:21.859
It's like a guy
offered me $100,000
for these once.

39:21.985 --> 39:25.028
And you didn't sell them?
No, if I ever need
the money that bad,

39:25.113 --> 39:28.031
I can always call up
a rich old lady and give her
some sweet lovin', you know?

39:28.116 --> 39:29.992
That's what I'm all about.
Hey, what's up, Al?

39:30.160 --> 39:32.661
How you doing?
I'm on dialysis.

39:32.746 --> 39:35.372
Right on, buddy.
Hey, Al, this is Lindsey.

39:35.457 --> 39:37.708
Hi. Al Waterman.
Here, have a sponge.

39:37.792 --> 39:39.877
Thank you.
Al is the first guy
I ever met

39:39.961 --> 39:41.879
at my first
Red Sox game ever.
Really?

39:41.963 --> 39:45.007
Yeah, he's aged horribly.
Hey, the Belnaps.

39:45.091 --> 39:47.801
This is Artie. Viv.
This is Lindsey.
Hello.

39:47.886 --> 39:49.303
Hi, Lindsey.
Hello.

39:49.429 --> 39:51.638
Been divorced 20 years,
still share the seats.
Really.

39:51.723 --> 39:53.599
Hey, Ben.
Sheri!

39:53.725 --> 39:56.310
How you doing?
Where's Teresa?
She's right here.

39:56.644 --> 39:59.021
Oh, my God.
What happened?
You look fantastic!

39:59.230 --> 40:02.232
I lost 200 pounds.
I had my stomach stapled shut.

40:02.358 --> 40:05.319
A doctor
or you did it yourself?
Oh, real funny.

40:05.987 --> 40:07.404
Hey!

40:09.699 --> 40:11.700
This is quite a little group
you have here.

40:11.785 --> 40:14.661
Well, it's
my summer family.

40:14.746 --> 40:18.707
[Boy]
For the land of the free

40:19.334 --> 40:25.547
And the home of the brave

40:25.632 --> 40:29.635
[Crowd Cheering]
[Announcer] Let's hear it
for Jordan Leandre.

40:30.220 --> 40:34.181
Ladies and gentlemen,
throwing out
the first ball today,

40:34.265 --> 40:37.226
New England's own
Stephen King.

40:37.602 --> 40:40.354
[Crowd Cheering]

40:40.438 --> 40:42.564
[Announcer]
Right down the middle.

40:46.736 --> 40:49.488
Did you tell Schuyler?
Okay, all right, listen.

40:49.572 --> 40:53.033
Um, excuse me.
What time is the game over?

40:53.117 --> 40:55.202
Uh, it's not like
a Broadway musical

40:55.286 --> 40:56.495
where it ends with
a big Hawaiian number.

40:56.579 --> 40:59.039
It's like you're missing
all the ambience
and all the fun.

40:59.123 --> 41:01.041
I know.
The players
are right there.

41:01.125 --> 41:04.086
I have a meeting at 5:30
and had to leave work at noon
to meet you here,

41:04.212 --> 41:06.880
so my people
aren't prepared.
Right. Okay.

41:09.717 --> 41:11.802
You know what?
I left work early,

41:11.886 --> 41:14.555
so you're gonna have to
figure it out for yourself,
and I'll call you later.

41:14.639 --> 41:16.265
[Announcer]
Wakefield.

41:23.398 --> 41:24.439
[Groans]

41:26.651 --> 41:28.402
That's a foul.

41:28.486 --> 41:31.446
What makes that a foul?
See that foul pole there?

41:31.531 --> 41:34.032
That's Pesky's Pole.
That's this guy
Johnny Pesky.

41:44.252 --> 41:45.377
Yeah!

41:59.893 --> 42:02.561
Hey, what are you doing
on Saturday?

42:02.645 --> 42:04.605
Mm, you tell me.

42:07.025 --> 42:09.192
You know what's really great
about baseball?
Hmm?

42:09.277 --> 42:11.111
You can't fake it.

42:11.195 --> 42:14.031
Anything else in life,
you don't have to
be great in.

42:14.115 --> 42:16.199
Business, music, art...
I mean, you can get lucky.

42:16.326 --> 42:18.660
Really?
Yeah, you can fool everyone
for a while, you know?

42:18.745 --> 42:20.662
It's like...
Not... Not baseball.

42:20.747 --> 42:22.789
You can either
hit a curveball
or you can't.

42:22.916 --> 42:25.667
That's the way
it works, you know?
Hmm.

42:25.752 --> 42:30.339
You could have a lucky day,
sure, but you can't have
a lucky career.

42:30.632 --> 42:33.467
It's a little like math.
It's orderly.

42:33.676 --> 42:36.845
Win or lose, it's fair.
It all adds up.

42:37.138 --> 42:41.141
It's, like, not as confusing
or as ambiguous as, uh...

42:41.225 --> 42:43.226
Life?
Yeah.

42:44.187 --> 42:46.480
It's... It's safe.

42:49.776 --> 42:51.985
Oh, yeah! Yeah!

42:54.530 --> 42:57.157
[Whooping]

42:57.659 --> 42:58.784
Hey.
Hi.

42:58.868 --> 43:00.369
What, did you buy out
the bookstore?

43:00.453 --> 43:02.788
Actually, I bought
every book they had
on the Red Sox,

43:02.872 --> 43:05.499
because I'm tired of being
the most ignorant person here.

43:05.583 --> 43:08.835
Now who is
Carl Yaz-a-strezem...

43:08.920 --> 43:12.214
[All] Yastrzemski.
[Mouthing Words]

43:12.340 --> 43:14.800
She's not a genius,
this one.
No.

43:15.343 --> 43:20.222
Johnny Damon!
You got the sweetest ass
in the league!

43:22.684 --> 43:24.267
Very nice.

43:26.813 --> 43:30.065
[Scoffs]
Do you believe in this?
"The Curse of the Bambino"?

43:30.149 --> 43:31.692
Hey, that's not funny.
That's enough of that.

43:31.776 --> 43:33.193
But Babe Ruth
was the Bambino.

43:33.277 --> 43:35.195
That's right.
He played for the Red Sox.

43:35.279 --> 43:37.823
They were great.
I mean, they were
the Yankees.

43:37.907 --> 43:41.535
They won the World Series
in 1912, 1915,

43:41.619 --> 43:43.620
1916, 1918.

43:43.705 --> 43:46.123
They were royalty.
The elite.

43:46.207 --> 43:49.251
Al should know.
He was there actually.
He's 136 years old.

43:49.335 --> 43:53.964
He looks great for his age.
1919, their miserable,
greedy pig of a boss

43:54.048 --> 43:57.467
decides to sell Babe Ruth
to the Yankees to finance
a Broadway musical.

43:57.552 --> 44:00.220
No, no, Nanette.
I would never ever
see that piece of crap.

44:00.805 --> 44:04.891
And since 1918,
the Red Sox have not won
a World Series.

44:04.976 --> 44:07.227
Yeah, the Yankees
have won 26.

44:07.311 --> 44:11.231
And the thing is
the Sox don't just lose,
they raise it to an art form.

44:11.315 --> 44:13.650
Tony C.,
best young player in baseball,

44:13.735 --> 44:17.612
catches one in the eye at 22,
he's finished at 26.

44:17.697 --> 44:20.866
Armbrister runs into
Carlton Fisk,
costs us the Series.

44:20.950 --> 44:22.951
Bucky friggin' Dent.
[Viv Groans]

44:23.036 --> 44:26.038
You remember the time
Roger Moret went catatonic?

44:26.122 --> 44:28.248
The grounds crew
had to carry him out
in a wheelbarrow.

44:28.332 --> 44:30.250
Buckner.
[All Groan]

44:30.334 --> 44:32.669
Grady little sticking
with Pedro
in the eighth inning.

44:32.754 --> 44:36.423
Ooh, stop it.
You're killing me here.

44:36.799 --> 44:39.801
And that, milady,
is the Curse of the Bambino.

44:39.886 --> 44:42.512
[Announcer]
Number 19, Gabe Kapler.

44:51.939 --> 44:54.816
Okay, I'm ready.
Let's go meet Mom and Dad.

44:56.360 --> 44:57.486
[Scoffs]

44:59.113 --> 45:00.697
Nothing.

45:00.782 --> 45:04.409
A laugh? A giggle?
This is not
a man's closet.

45:04.535 --> 45:07.079
What do you mean?
You have one pair
of dress shoes.

45:07.163 --> 45:09.873
You're like a man-boy.
Half man, half boy.

45:09.957 --> 45:12.459
You should see the way
my sister's husband dresses.

45:12.543 --> 45:16.755
He had a professional
come in and do his closet.
It's like suit, suit, suit...

45:16.839 --> 45:19.091
All right, okay, okay.
I see what this is all about.

45:19.175 --> 45:21.968
You want your parents
to like me more than they
like your brother-in-law.

45:23.179 --> 45:25.430
No, it's not...
Yes!

45:26.474 --> 45:31.478
[Sighs]
Is it so horrible that
I want my parents to like you?

45:33.397 --> 45:37.150
Okay. I think we have
enough stuff in this closet.
We can fool 'em.

45:37.985 --> 45:39.152
[Mom]
He looks like a skunk.

45:39.403 --> 45:41.238
You're the one that told me
to grow it out.

45:41.322 --> 45:44.908
Well, what else could I say?
It looked ridiculous on you.
A man your age...

45:44.992 --> 45:47.702
Now, I understand
that you're a teacher, right?
You were?

45:47.787 --> 45:49.496
Yes, for 27 years.

45:49.580 --> 45:52.082
And, okay, now you're
the principal, right?
Mm-hmm.

45:52.166 --> 45:55.168
And you...
Did you ever tell me
what your dad does?

45:55.294 --> 45:59.422
I sell golf carts.
Wow. Okay, that gives us
nothing to talk about.

45:59.507 --> 46:01.424
I don't really know much
about it.

46:01.509 --> 46:04.553
That's funny,
'cause every other guy
she's gone out with

46:04.637 --> 46:06.721
has tried to get
a free golf cart
out of me.

46:06.806 --> 46:10.225
No, I like golf. Great sport.
It's just I don't really
get out much, you know?

46:10.476 --> 46:11.852
We love it.
Yeah?

46:11.936 --> 46:14.062
They play all the time.

46:14.147 --> 46:16.648
We tried to get on
the country club here,
but it's very difficult.

46:16.732 --> 46:20.235
It's almost impossible.
I had to call the manufacturer
of my golf carts,

46:20.361 --> 46:23.113
a guy named
Dave Johnson, and said...
Jensen.

46:23.197 --> 46:25.407
No, Dave... Dave Johnson.
Jensen.

46:25.533 --> 46:28.535
Jensen?
Hi. Sorry we're late. He was
watching the Red Sox game.

46:28.619 --> 46:31.163
How'd they do?
No, no.
La, la, la, la, la!

46:31.247 --> 46:33.165
Help me! Help me!
Help me!
What's wrong?

46:33.249 --> 46:36.209
Oh, help me! Help me!
Help me! La la la la!

46:36.294 --> 46:38.670
[Man, Indistinct]
La la la la.
La la la la.

46:38.754 --> 46:40.672
[Making Noises]
Okay. Okay.

46:40.756 --> 46:43.049
It was awesome.
Struck out the side.

46:43.134 --> 46:46.344
Okay, it stopped.
It stopped. Stop it!
Stop it! Stop it!

46:48.222 --> 46:50.473
Whew!
Um...

46:50.600 --> 46:53.685
Thank you.
Yeah. Ben tapes
the Red Sox games,

46:54.228 --> 46:55.645
so he doesn't wanna
know the score.

46:55.730 --> 46:58.815
And he can't
cover his own ears 'cause
he's got lobster fingers,

46:58.900 --> 46:59.900
so I do it.

47:00.985 --> 47:02.903
That's sweet.

47:07.450 --> 47:10.577
Hey, how'd it go last night?
Fabulous.

47:10.745 --> 47:11.995
Mr. Myerson
wants to see you.

47:13.122 --> 47:16.666
Oh, God. If one of
the windows would open,
I would jump.

47:16.751 --> 47:18.585
And your mom's
on line one.

47:20.004 --> 47:24.507
Hi, Mom. Hi.
Listen, where are you?
Can I call you back?

47:26.010 --> 47:28.386
What? You had
a 10:00 a.m. Flight.

47:32.058 --> 47:34.559
My Ben?
Yes, he has been great.

47:34.644 --> 47:37.771
He took us out to breakfast.
Right now he's washing
your father's balls.

47:37.980 --> 47:39.022
What?

47:41.484 --> 47:43.193
Here's one.
Thanks, Ben.

47:43.277 --> 47:45.820
He got us a 10:00 a.m.
Tee time at the country club.

47:47.114 --> 47:48.615
How?

47:49.450 --> 47:52.786
One of his student's fathers
has something to do
with the sprinklers.

47:52.870 --> 47:55.121
Can I talk to him
for a second?
Oh, sure.

47:55.206 --> 47:56.998
Benny? Lindsey.

47:57.083 --> 47:59.167
Oh, thanks.
Hi, Linds.

48:00.002 --> 48:02.128
Hey, what are you doing?

48:02.463 --> 48:03.797
Took a sick day.

48:05.633 --> 48:08.843
All right.
Well, I'll see you
tonight then.

48:08.928 --> 48:11.054
All right. Bye-bye.
Honey...

48:11.138 --> 48:15.267
Uh, sweetheart,
don't talk in my backswing.

48:15.393 --> 48:18.061
Well, you were
lined up wrong.
I wasn't lined up, I...

48:18.145 --> 48:20.522
Please, don't talk
in my backswing. You know
better than that.

48:20.606 --> 48:23.900
Just take a mulligan.
Lighten up.

48:23.985 --> 48:26.569
He's so short with me.
I know. I know.
But you know what?

48:26.696 --> 48:29.406
You talked in his backswing.
Did you talk in his backswing?
Yes, I did.

48:29.490 --> 48:32.033
Don't even look at him.
Look this way. Let him swing.
Okay.

48:39.041 --> 48:42.460
[Crowd Cheering]

48:46.757 --> 48:48.758
Where it began

48:49.802 --> 48:51.928
Manny! Manny! Manny!

48:52.013 --> 48:53.179
I can't begin to know when

48:54.432 --> 48:57.892
But then I know
it's growin' strong

49:02.106 --> 49:03.898
Wasn't the spring

49:05.860 --> 49:08.445
And spring
became the summer

49:09.697 --> 49:12.866
Who'd have believed
you'd come along

49:16.287 --> 49:18.997
Hand

