This is exactly
what you liked about me.

01:05:47.694 --> 01:05:50.779
That I was capable
of having a passionate
commitment with something.

01:05:50.864 --> 01:05:52.489
Uh, a devotion.

01:05:52.574 --> 01:05:56.493
Yes, but you feel it
for the Red Sox, and I was
hoping that someday

01:05:56.578 --> 01:05:58.662
you might redirect that.

01:06:01.666 --> 01:06:04.793
All those things
that you feel
for that team,

01:06:04.878 --> 01:06:08.047
I feel them too,
for you.

01:06:23.772 --> 01:06:26.982
You know what she's saying
to me, Ryan? She's saying
I have an addiction.

01:06:27.067 --> 01:06:29.443
Really? Well, you work
90 hours a week.

01:06:29.527 --> 01:06:33.447
You know, that... But I guess
that addiction's more
socially acceptable, you know.

01:06:33.531 --> 01:06:35.240
Am I wrong?
Am I wrong?

01:06:35.325 --> 01:06:38.660
Well, nobody's really wrong
in these situations.

01:06:38.745 --> 01:06:40.913
I mean, you have
wants and needs.

01:06:40.997 --> 01:06:43.415
She likewise.

01:06:43.792 --> 01:06:46.418
Wait for
your pitch, Miosky!

01:06:48.588 --> 01:06:51.382
But she's great.
She's great.
[Ball Strikes Bat]

01:06:51.466 --> 01:06:53.467
Definitely the best girl
I've ever gone out with.

01:06:53.551 --> 01:06:57.137
The... The smartest,
the funniest,
the best-looking.

01:06:57.222 --> 01:06:59.431
The sex is like
the... Well...

01:07:01.434 --> 01:07:04.103
But there's a reason why
she's 30 and not married.

01:07:04.187 --> 01:07:05.854
I mean, you gotta see
the big deal
she's making about

01:07:05.939 --> 01:07:07.523
her friend's
birthday party.

01:07:07.607 --> 01:07:10.192
Oh, God. She's making
a federal case about it.

01:07:10.276 --> 01:07:14.071
I'm, like, hey, what if
I had to work that night?
What if I had a second job?

01:07:14.155 --> 01:07:17.241
You know?
What if I was doing
charity work? Is that cool?

01:07:17.325 --> 01:07:19.368
What if I'm, like,
finishing a painting?

01:07:19.452 --> 01:07:20.869
Is that...
You understand me now?

01:07:21.037 --> 01:07:22.871
See my point?
It's not the time.

01:07:22.956 --> 01:07:25.332
It's she doesn't respect
how I'm spending my time.

01:07:25.417 --> 01:07:27.876
And now she expects me
to miss a Yankees game?

01:07:27.961 --> 01:07:29.878
[Laughs]
Whatever.

01:07:29.963 --> 01:07:32.339
[Man]
Let's go, Murph.
You're up.

01:07:33.633 --> 01:07:36.218
All right,
Mr. Wrightman.
I gotta bat.

01:07:36.302 --> 01:07:38.804
Let me just leave you
with this thought.

01:07:38.888 --> 01:07:39.972
You love the Sox.

01:07:41.141 --> 01:07:43.350
But have they ever
loved you back?

01:07:48.940 --> 01:07:52.734
Who are you, Dr. Phil?
Get out of here. Go hit...
Go swing the bat.

01:07:56.239 --> 01:07:57.990
[Man Announcing]
The Red Sox
started off tonight

01:07:58.074 --> 01:08:00.492
three games behind
the Yankees.

01:08:00.577 --> 01:08:05.539
Pedro delivers. The ball is
lined over Bellhorn's head
into right center field.

01:08:05.623 --> 01:08:10.002
That'll get another run across
as the Yankees extend
their lead.

01:08:10.086 --> 01:08:13.672
[Jazz]

01:08:15.633 --> 01:08:17.843
[Jazz Continues]

01:08:19.929 --> 01:08:24.183
Benny boy,
I still can't believe
you're not at the Yankee game.

01:08:24.267 --> 01:08:27.060
Yeah, well, if the Yankees
looked that good in a dress,

01:08:27.312 --> 01:08:29.688
I'd be at the game.

01:08:40.992 --> 01:08:42.993
[Glass Clinking]

01:08:44.953 --> 01:08:48.040
There's no way to measure
what she is worth.

01:08:48.124 --> 01:08:50.917
I'm the luckiest man
on the face of the Earth.

01:08:51.002 --> 01:08:53.295
[Crowd Murmuring]
Her, uh...

01:08:53.379 --> 01:08:56.256
Hang on. Hang on.
Okay. "I'm the luckiest man
on the face of the Earth.

01:08:56.341 --> 01:08:58.591
"Her face, her form,
her sweet, loving smile.

01:08:59.093 --> 01:09:02.554
And she even lets me
dance around in her panties
once in a while."

01:09:02.639 --> 01:09:04.515
[All Gasp]
My parents are here!

01:09:04.599 --> 01:09:08.060
[Cheering]
Really embarrassing.
Really bad.

01:09:08.310 --> 01:09:09.937
I love you,
birthday girl.

01:09:10.229 --> 01:09:11.522
I love you.

01:09:12.982 --> 01:09:14.441
[Big Band Jazz]

01:09:26.120 --> 01:09:27.746
[Pop]

01:09:28.247 --> 01:09:31.667
And so the conversation
turned

01:09:32.252 --> 01:09:35.212
Until the sun went down

01:09:36.046 --> 01:09:39.591
And many fantasies
were learned

01:09:40.718 --> 01:09:42.636
On that day

01:09:42.720 --> 01:09:45.514
Keep feeling fascination

01:09:45.598 --> 01:09:48.267
[Jazz]

01:09:49.935 --> 01:09:53.188
Have I a hope
or half a chance

01:09:53.273 --> 01:09:57.276
To even ask
if I could dance with you

01:09:59.237 --> 01:10:00.779
Yoo-hoo

01:10:01.990 --> 01:10:06.577
Would you greet me
or politely turn away

01:10:08.204 --> 01:10:13.041
Would there suddenly be
sunshine on a cold and

01:10:13.126 --> 01:10:14.376
[Vocalizing: "Dirty Water"]

01:10:14.460 --> 01:10:17.170
[Man On Radio]
Yankee bats
have come alive tonight.

01:10:17.255 --> 01:10:19.631
What's up, my man?
Oh. The game.

01:10:19.716 --> 01:10:22.718
No, no. Hey.
It's fine. It's fine.

01:10:23.136 --> 01:10:24.720
It's fine.
Okay.

01:10:24.804 --> 01:10:27.598
[Man] None have been
successful so far against
this powerful Yankee offense.

01:10:27.682 --> 01:10:29.641
6-0, Yankees.
[Chuckles]

01:10:29.726 --> 01:10:31.602
[Man] Timlin ready to face
the left fielder,
Hideki Matsui.

01:10:31.686 --> 01:10:33.061
Timlin to the belt.

01:10:33.146 --> 01:10:34.813
Here's the pitch.
[Ball Dings Against Bat]

01:10:34.897 --> 01:10:37.316
Swung on.
A drive hit high and deep.

01:10:37.400 --> 01:10:39.401
And this one is gone.

01:10:39.485 --> 01:10:42.112
7-0.
Matsui has hit his second
home run of the night.

01:10:42.196 --> 01:10:44.323
Hey. It's only a game.

01:10:47.869 --> 01:10:49.828
That was like...

01:10:50.997 --> 01:10:53.415
Yeah.

01:10:53.499 --> 01:10:55.667
I mean...
I mean, you were...

01:10:56.669 --> 01:10:59.046
Thank you.

01:10:59.130 --> 01:11:02.007
Not... Not just physically.

01:11:02.091 --> 01:11:06.094
I mean, it felt like...
Like we were...

01:11:07.847 --> 01:11:09.848
Mm-hmm.
[Chuckles]

01:11:12.185 --> 01:11:15.145
I think this might be
the greatest night of my life.

01:11:19.776 --> 01:11:21.985
[Phone Rings]

01:11:28.785 --> 01:11:31.078
Hello.
[Men Shouting]

01:11:31.162 --> 01:11:35.040
Hold on.
I think it's Troy.
It's really noisy.

01:11:36.542 --> 01:11:38.877
Hey. Do you want
some food?
Yeah.

01:11:38.961 --> 01:11:41.421
Okay.
Hello?

01:11:42.674 --> 01:11:43.799
Hey, what's that noise?

01:11:44.384 --> 01:11:46.343
Ben, we won! We won!

01:11:46.886 --> 01:11:49.346
We were losing 7-0
in the bottom of the ninth!

01:11:49.430 --> 01:11:51.682
We scored eight runs!
Ten straight hits!

01:11:51.766 --> 01:11:55.519
It was unbelievable, man!
It's the greatest night
in the history of Fenway Park!

01:11:55.603 --> 01:11:59.147
Can you hear this?
It's bedlam here, man!

01:11:59.232 --> 01:12:03.068
Yes! By... by the end,
the stands were
literally shaking!

01:12:03.152 --> 01:12:04.236
The fire marshal
had to get the...

01:12:04.529 --> 01:12:06.780
[Indistinct]
To stop jumping up and down!

01:12:08.658 --> 01:12:10.826
The one game you missed!

01:12:10.910 --> 01:12:13.870
You missed
the greatest game ever!

01:12:13.996 --> 01:12:16.498
[Yelling]
[Beeps Off]

01:12:18.126 --> 01:12:21.586
[Cheering On TV]
This is an historic night,
Natalie.

01:12:21.671 --> 01:12:27.426
And word is these
tickets stubs are already
getting $200 on the street.

01:12:27.927 --> 01:12:31.680
I have seen at least
a dozen women celebrating
topless in the streets.

01:12:31.764 --> 01:12:36.017
Moments ago I witnessed
a nun dancing on top of
a moving vehicle.

01:12:36.102 --> 01:12:40.188
I have seen police officers
toasting beer
with underage children.

01:12:40.273 --> 01:12:41.565
It is absolute bedlam
down here.

01:12:41.649 --> 01:12:44.276
Right now I think
we're witnessing
the largest conga line ever.

01:12:44.360 --> 01:12:46.528
I tell you what.
If you are not down here
right now,

01:12:46.612 --> 01:12:48.447
you're missing
one heck of a party.

01:12:50.074 --> 01:12:52.033
[Whimpers]

01:12:52.118 --> 01:12:56.705
There are three eggs
in Spanish omelet

01:12:56.789 --> 01:13:00.000
[Whistling]

01:13:00.293 --> 01:13:02.836
Hi. Would you like
an omelet?

01:13:04.464 --> 01:13:06.465
They... Won.

01:13:06.549 --> 01:13:08.550
The Red Sox?

01:13:08.634 --> 01:13:11.511
Oh, good!
This really is your night.

01:13:11.596 --> 01:13:12.929
No. You don't understand.

01:13:13.014 --> 01:13:15.807
They scored eight runs
in the bottom
of the ninth to win 8-7.

01:13:15.892 --> 01:13:19.186
It was the best game ever.
I... I can't...

01:13:19.270 --> 01:13:21.271
I... I never miss a game.

01:13:21.355 --> 01:13:23.607
Ever.
This is like a nightmare.

01:13:24.025 --> 01:13:27.027
No, this is beyond that.
This is like a punishment
from God or something.

01:13:27.111 --> 01:13:29.863
Two minutes ago you said
this was the best night
of your life.

01:13:29.947 --> 01:13:32.199
Yeah. Two minutes ago
it was.

01:13:33.034 --> 01:13:35.243
Hey. I didn't tell you
not to go.

01:13:35.328 --> 01:13:37.204
Oh, no. No, no.
Of course not. No.

01:13:37.288 --> 01:13:39.915
You had nothing to do with it.
I just suddenly had a whim,

01:13:39.999 --> 01:13:43.460
after 11 years of never
missing an inning, to suddenly
not go to a Yankees game.

01:13:43.878 --> 01:13:46.046
[Lindsey] Hey.
[Whimpers]

01:13:47.465 --> 01:13:50.759
Wasn't it you yourself
that said just tonight,

01:13:50.843 --> 01:13:52.177
"It's only a game"?

01:13:52.595 --> 01:13:55.055
Oh, that's great.
That's great.
Pile it on. Yeah.

01:13:55.181 --> 01:13:58.183
Kick me when I'm down.
That's great.
It is just a game.

01:13:58.351 --> 01:14:00.477
Clearly, it's not
just a game!

01:14:00.853 --> 01:14:04.147
If it was,
then obviously I wouldn't
care about it this much.

01:14:04.232 --> 01:14:05.690
Twenty-three years.

01:14:05.900 --> 01:14:08.193
Do you still care about
anything you cared about
23 years ago?

01:14:09.153 --> 01:14:11.488
How about 10?
How about five?

01:14:11.572 --> 01:14:14.533
Name me a single thing
that you've cared about
for 23 years.

01:14:16.285 --> 01:14:21.289
Yeah. No, um,
there isn't actually anything
I've wanted for 23 years

01:14:21.457 --> 01:14:23.959
because 23 years ago
I was seven,

01:14:24.043 --> 01:14:28.713
and if I still wanted to marry
Scott Baio, I would think that
my life went terribly wrong.

01:14:31.008 --> 01:14:34.010
I... I just thought tonight
was so different.

01:14:34.095 --> 01:14:36.096
You broke my heart, Ben.

01:14:37.181 --> 01:14:38.849
Hey.

01:14:51.445 --> 01:14:53.530
[Shouting, Faint]

01:14:55.491 --> 01:14:57.534
Awesome!
Whoo-hoo!

01:14:57.618 --> 01:14:59.536
Wow!

01:14:59.620 --> 01:15:02.414
Wow!
Yeah, baby!

01:15:06.377 --> 01:15:08.753
[Man Announcing]
Well, the Red Sox's
once-promising season

01:15:08.838 --> 01:15:11.590
has certainly taken
a turn for the worse.

01:15:12.758 --> 01:15:17.137
Losing the last three games,
and today trailing
to the Texas Rangers.

01:15:17.722 --> 01:15:19.180
Curse of the Bambino.

01:15:19.265 --> 01:15:21.683
To think we quit our jobs
for that road trip.

01:15:21.767 --> 01:15:23.685
It's not a curse.

01:15:23.769 --> 01:15:27.272
Did you know the Titanic
sank the same week
Fenway Park opened?

01:15:27.607 --> 01:15:29.316
April 1912.

01:15:34.530 --> 01:15:36.615
Oh, you...

01:15:36.699 --> 01:15:38.992
[Crowd Booing]
Well, that's it.

01:15:39.076 --> 01:15:41.077
The Yankees officially
clinch the division.

01:15:41.162 --> 01:15:44.706
Seven years in a row now,
we finish with our faces
in their butts.

01:15:44.790 --> 01:15:48.418
Hey, hey, hey.
It's not time to jump off
the Tobin Bridge yet, okay?

01:15:48.502 --> 01:15:50.045
We still have the wild card.

01:15:50.129 --> 01:15:53.632
Oh, that's easy.
First we gotta beat Oakland
or Anaheim, on the road.

01:15:53.716 --> 01:15:56.176
Then we gotta play
the Yankees
in the house of pain.

01:15:56.469 --> 01:15:59.012
Why do we inflict this
on ourselves?

01:15:59.096 --> 01:16:00.805
Why?

01:16:00.890 --> 01:16:02.807
I'll tell you why.

01:16:02.975 --> 01:16:05.352
'Cause the Red Sox
never let you down.

01:16:05.937 --> 01:16:08.772
Huh?
That's right. I mean...

01:16:08.856 --> 01:16:11.608
Why? 'Cause they haven't
won a world series
in a century or so?

01:16:11.692 --> 01:16:14.110
So what?
They're here.

01:16:14.195 --> 01:16:16.571
Every April, they're here.

01:16:16.656 --> 01:16:20.116
At 1:05 or at 7:05,
there is a game.

01:16:20.201 --> 01:16:23.620
And if it gets rained out,
guess what.
They make it up to you.

01:16:23.955 --> 01:16:25.914
Does anyone else
in your life do that?

01:16:25.998 --> 01:16:27.874
The Red Sox
don't get divorced.

01:16:28.167 --> 01:16:31.378
This is a real family.
This is the family
that's here for you.

01:16:31.462 --> 01:16:34.214
You know, I don't ask her
to give up her family, do I?

01:16:34.298 --> 01:16:38.385
Come on!
Let's get some runs!
Let's get some runs!

01:16:38.719 --> 01:16:42.180
You know the best part?
I can get over her
because I am a Red Sox fan.

01:16:42.974 --> 01:16:46.059
I mean, I'm tough.
I've been through a lot
in this park, man.

01:16:46.143 --> 01:16:48.019
I can take this.

01:16:48.104 --> 01:16:50.188
Because I am bulletproof.

01:16:50.856 --> 01:16:52.273
[Music]
Carl Yastrzemski
Carl Yastrzemski

01:16:52.358 --> 01:16:54.067
[Announcer
On TV, Indistinct]

01:16:54.151 --> 01:16:57.904
Carl Yastrzemski
the man we call Yaz
we love him

01:16:57.989 --> 01:16:59.155
Carl Yastrzemski

01:16:59.240 --> 01:17:01.282
[Man Announcing]
Behind the bag!
It gets through Buckner!

01:17:01.367 --> 01:17:02.409
Carl Yastrzemski

01:17:02.493 --> 01:17:05.161
Here comes Knight,
and the Mets win it!

01:17:05.246 --> 01:17:06.871
[Continues]

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:11.251
[Continues]
[Knocking]

01:17:11.335 --> 01:17:13.753
[Troy]
Open the door, man!

01:17:13.879 --> 01:17:15.839
[Yelling]
Little roller
up along first.

01:17:15.923 --> 01:17:19.926
Behind the bag!
It gets through Buckner!

01:17:20.011 --> 01:17:22.554
Oh, my God.
The Buckner game?

01:17:22.638 --> 01:17:24.472
I thought you took
that away from him!
I did!

01:17:24.557 --> 01:17:25.598
Behind the bag!
It gets through Buckner!

01:17:25.683 --> 01:17:26.933
Carl Yastrzemski

01:17:27.018 --> 01:17:28.977
The man they call Yaz

01:17:29.061 --> 01:17:30.562
And the Mets win it!

01:17:39.572 --> 01:17:42.657
It wasn't just Buckner.
Stanley screwed him.

01:17:42.742 --> 01:17:44.075
He didn't cover first.

01:17:44.410 --> 01:17:47.370
Where'd you get this?
I... I don't remember.

01:17:47.496 --> 01:17:50.040
Don't lie to me.
Right. Do you have
any more of these?

01:17:50.124 --> 01:17:52.083
Huh? Where's your stash?

01:17:52.418 --> 01:17:54.252
Ben, this isn't
helping you.

01:17:55.004 --> 01:17:57.881
You understand that?
This solves nothing!

01:17:58.591 --> 01:18:00.383
Ben, look at you.

01:18:00.468 --> 01:18:01.926
Yeah, leave me alone.

01:18:04.221 --> 01:18:07.265
All right.
Let's clean him up.
[Gerard] Come on.

01:18:07.349 --> 01:18:10.060
I let her down.
Let's go.

01:18:10.144 --> 01:18:12.270
I am the Red Sox.
You're not
the Red Sox.

01:18:12.354 --> 01:18:14.481
I am the Red Sox.
You're not the Red Sox.

01:18:15.608 --> 01:18:17.275
Get him up on the shoulder
there, Gerard.

01:18:17.359 --> 01:18:19.486
I got the
shoulder right now.

01:18:19.570 --> 01:18:22.906
What are you doing?
Relax. I'm a doctor.

01:18:22.990 --> 01:18:26.993
Yeah, well, not to pry,
Doc, but why are you
shaving my balls?

01:18:28.871 --> 01:18:32.040
Well, if you don't
want me to...
No, I don't want you to.

01:18:32.124 --> 01:18:34.125
Whatever.
Hey.

01:18:40.132 --> 01:18:42.008
[Man #1]
Bottom of the 10th.

01:18:42.093 --> 01:18:44.719
[Man #2]
Swing and a fly ball
to left field! Way back!

01:18:44.804 --> 01:18:47.347
Way back!
The Red Sox are going

01:18:47.431 --> 01:18:50.141
to the American League
Championship Series

01:18:50.226 --> 01:18:52.936
on the back of David Ortiz!

01:18:53.020 --> 01:18:54.604
All right. You've been
waiting all year for this.

01:18:54.688 --> 01:18:57.941
The Yankees, Red Sox,
the best rivalry in sports
starts tonight.

01:18:58.025 --> 01:19:00.443
8:00, Yankee stadium.
Let's get it on.

01:19:00.736 --> 01:19:03.613
[Man Announcing]
The 2-2 pitch.
Mueller back to Rivera.

01:19:03.697 --> 01:19:06.908
To second for one.
On to first. Double play!

01:19:06.992 --> 01:19:09.077
And the Yankees take game one.

01:19:09.912 --> 01:19:13.248
[Man Announcing]
The Yankees are a strike away.
Here's a 1-2 pitch.

01:19:13.332 --> 01:19:16.417
Struck him out swinging
that'll wrap it up.

01:19:16.502 --> 01:19:20.421
For the second night in a row,
the Yankees have beaten
the Red Sox.

01:19:21.507 --> 01:19:24.425
Here's a 2-0.
Mueller flies to center.

01:19:24.510 --> 01:19:27.929
Bernie Williams is there,
and the Yankees have won it.

01:19:28.013 --> 01:19:31.141
The end of a long night,
and perhaps the end for
the Boston Red Sox,

01:19:31.225 --> 01:19:35.061
losing tonight 19-8,
now falling in the series
three games to none.

01:19:35.146 --> 01:19:37.647
I mean, this thing is over.
They keep swinging the bats

01:19:37.731 --> 01:19:39.691
the way they are, Don,
this thing's done.

01:19:44.196 --> 01:19:46.531
19-8. Good God.

01:19:46.824 --> 01:19:49.367
Will you stop
saying that? Okay?

01:19:50.202 --> 01:19:53.079
Now, who we pitching
tomorrow?
What's the difference?

01:19:53.164 --> 01:19:55.623
We're losing
three games to nothing
to the Yankees.

01:19:55.708 --> 01:19:58.543
In a hundred years,
no team in the play-offs
has ever come back from that.

